    {
      "text": "A 45-year-old female comes to the clinic with a reddish patch on her tongue, as shown in the figure. She gives a history of chewing pan masala for more than 15 years. She has no difficulty in opening her mouth and has no other comorbidities. What is the most probable diagnosis?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Oral submucosal fibrosis",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Erythroplakia",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Plummer-Vinson syndrome",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Leukoerythroplakia",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. Erythroplakia",
