      "text": "A patient presents with 2.5 cm ulceroproliferative adenoid cystic carcinoma on the left side of the hard palate. Imaging shows no evidence of bone invasion or lymph node involvement. Which of the following is the most appropriate management strategy?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Wide local excision with frozen section control",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Partial maxillectomy with ipsilateral neck dissection",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Partial maxillectomy without neck dissection",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Radiotherapy alone",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C. Partial maxillectomy without neck dissection",
